{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":705,"text":"In System D, this"},{"time":2930,"text":"is a store,"},{"time":4977,"text":"and what I mean by that is that this is a photograph"},{"time":7304,"text":"I took in Makoko, shantytown in Lagos, Nigeria."},{"time":12619,"text":"It's built over the lagoon, and there are no streets"},{"time":15002,"text":"where there can be stores to shop,"},{"time":16818,"text":"and so the store comes to you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":18708,"text":"And in the same community,"},{"time":20493,"text":"this is business synergy."},{"time":22245,"text":"This is the boat that that lady was paddling around in,"},{"time":26351,"text":"and this artisan makes the boat and the paddles"},{"time":29091,"text":"and sells directly"},{"time":30396,"text":"to the people who need the boat and the paddles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32560,"text":"And this is a global business."},{"time":34742,"text":"Ogandiro smokes fish in Makoko in Lagos,"},{"time":38868,"text":"and I asked her, \"Where does the fish come from?\""},{"time":41829,"text":"And I thought she'd say, \"Oh, you know,"},{"time":44555,"text":"up the lagoon somewhere, or maybe across Africa,\""},{"time":47456,"text":"but you'll be happy to know she said"},{"time":48887,"text":"it came from here, it comes from the North Sea."},{"time":50944,"text":"It's caught here, frozen, shipped down to Lagos,"},{"time":53270,"text":"smoked, and sold for a tiny increment of profit"},{"time":56357,"text":"on the streets of Lagos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57879,"text":"And this is a business incubator."},{"time":59730,"text":"This is Olusosun dump, the largest garbage dump in Lagos,"},{"time":63432,"text":"and 2,000 people work here, and I found this out"},{"time":66503,"text":"from this fellow, Andrew Saboru."},{"time":68921,"text":"Andrew spent 16 years scavenging materials on the dump,"},{"time":73081,"text":"earned enough money to turn himself into a contract scaler,"},{"time":76309,"text":"which meant he carried a scale and went around and"},{"time":78919,"text":"weighed all the materials that people had scavenged"},{"time":81143,"text":"from the dump. Now he's a scrap dealer."},{"time":84166,"text":"That's his little depot behind him,"},{"time":86567,"text":"and he earns twice the Nigerian minimum wage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91078,"text":"This is a shopping mall."},{"time":93340,"text":"This is Oshodi Market in Lagos."},{"time":95515,"text":"Jorge Luis Borges had a story called \"The Aleph,\""},{"time":97861,"text":"and the Aleph is a point in the world"},{"time":99684,"text":"where absolutely everything exists,"},{"time":101979,"text":"and for me, this image is a point in the world"},{"time":104324,"text":"where absolutely everything exists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106788,"text":"So, what am I talking about when I talk about System D?"},{"time":109637,"text":"It's traditionally called the informal economy,"},{"time":111936,"text":"the underground economy, the black market."},{"time":115564,"text":"I don't conceive of it that way."},{"time":117857,"text":"I think it's really important to understand that something like"},{"time":120614,"text":"this is totally open. It's right there for you to find."},{"time":125094,"text":"All of this is happening openly, and aboveboard."},{"time":127821,"text":"There's nothing underground about it."},{"time":130343,"text":"It's our prejudgment that it's underground."}]},{"cues":[{"time":133725,"text":"I've pirated the term System D from the former French colonies."},{"time":138230,"text":"There's a word in French that is débrouillardise,"},{"time":141326,"text":"that means to be self-reliant,"},{"time":143446,"text":"and the former French colonies have turned that into"},{"time":146809,"text":"System D for the economy of self-reliance,"},{"time":149366,"text":"or the DIY economy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152624,"text":"But governments hate the DIY economy,"},{"time":155753,"text":"and that's why -- I took this picture in 2007,"},{"time":158997,"text":"and this is the same market in 2009 --"},{"time":163549,"text":"and I think, when the organizers of this conference"},{"time":165855,"text":"were talking about radical openness,"},{"time":167282,"text":"they didn't mean that the streets should be open"},{"time":169838,"text":"and the people should be gone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171581,"text":"I think what we have is a pickle problem."},{"time":175524,"text":"I had a friend who worked at a pickle factory,"},{"time":178464,"text":"and the cucumbers would come flying down"},{"time":180365,"text":"this conveyer belt, and his job was to pick off the ones"},{"time":184368,"text":"that didn't look so good and throw them in the bin"},{"time":186717,"text":"labeled \"relish\" where they'd be crushed and mixed"},{"time":188623,"text":"with vinegar and used for other kinds of profit."},{"time":191949,"text":"This is the pickle economy."},{"time":194260,"text":"We're all focusing on — this is a statistic from"},{"time":196765,"text":"earlier this month in the Financial Times —"},{"time":199344,"text":"we're all focusing on the luxury economy."},{"time":202887,"text":"It's worth 1.5 trillion dollars every year, and that's"},{"time":205630,"text":"a vast amount of money, right?"},{"time":207374,"text":"That's three times the Gross Domestic Product of Switzerland."},{"time":210622,"text":"So it's vast. But it should come with an asterisk,"},{"time":215420,"text":"and the asterisk is that it excludes two thirds of the workers"},{"time":219613,"text":"of the world."},{"time":220666,"text":"1.8 billion people around the world work"},{"time":224055,"text":"in the economy that is unregulated and informal."},{"time":229591,"text":"That's a huge number, and what does that mean?"},{"time":232871,"text":"Well, it means if it were united in a single political system,"},{"time":237624,"text":"one country, call it"},{"time":241879,"text":"\"The United Street Sellers Republic,\" the U.S.S.R.,"},{"time":244880,"text":"or \"Bazaaristan,\""},{"time":246713,"text":"it would be worth 10 trillion dollars every year,"},{"time":250989,"text":"and that would make it the second largest economy"},{"time":253045,"text":"in the world, after the United States."},{"time":255526,"text":"And given that projections are that the bulk"},{"time":258366,"text":"of economic growth over the next 15 years will come"},{"time":262031,"text":"from emerging economies in the developing world,"},{"time":265403,"text":"it could easily overtake the United States"},{"time":267534,"text":"and become the largest economy in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270900,"text":"So the implications of that are vast, because it means"},{"time":274435,"text":"that this is where employment is — 1.8 billion people —"},{"time":277958,"text":"and this is where we can create a more egalitarian world,"},{"time":282580,"text":"because people are actually able to earn money and live"},{"time":286551,"text":"and thrive, as Andrew Saboru did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":289546,"text":"Big businesses have recognized this,"},{"time":291707,"text":"and what's fascinating about this slide,"},{"time":293686,"text":"it's not that the guys can carry boxes on their heads"},{"time":295944,"text":"and run around without dropping them off."},{"time":298459,"text":"it's that the Gala sausage roll is a product that's made"},{"time":301554,"text":"by a global company called UAC foods"},{"time":304264,"text":"that's active throughout Africa and the Middle East,"},{"time":306831,"text":"but the Gala sausage roll is not sold in stores."},{"time":310520,"text":"UAC foods has recognized that it won't sell if it's in stores."},{"time":313857,"text":"It's only sold by a phalanx of street hawkers"},{"time":317962,"text":"who run around the streets of Lagos at bus stations"},{"time":320775,"text":"and in traffic jams and sell it as a snack,"},{"time":325248,"text":"and it's been sold that way for 40 years."},{"time":328270,"text":"It's a business plan for a corporation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330440,"text":"And it's not just in Africa."},{"time":332933,"text":"Here's Mr. Clean looking amorously at all the other"},{"time":336046,"text":"Procter &amp; Gamble products,"},{"time":337966,"text":"and Procter &amp; Gamble, you know,"},{"time":340414,"text":"the statistic always cited is that Wal-Mart"},{"time":342991,"text":"is their largest customer, and it's true, as one store,"},{"time":347847,"text":"Wal-Mart buys 15 percent, thus 15 percent"},{"time":351034,"text":"of Procter &amp; Gamble's business is with Wal-Mart,"},{"time":354134,"text":"but their largest market segment is something that they call"},{"time":357695,"text":"\"high frequency stores,\" which is all these tiny kiosks"},{"time":360615,"text":"and the lady in the canoe and all these other businesses"},{"time":363926,"text":"that exist in System D, the informal economy,"},{"time":369273,"text":"and Procter &amp; Gamble makes 20 percent of its money"},{"time":372671,"text":"from that market segment,"},{"time":374720,"text":"and it's the only market segment that's growing."},{"time":378156,"text":"So Procter &amp; Gamble says, \"We don't care whether a store"},{"time":381264,"text":"is incorporated or registered or anything like that."},{"time":384158,"text":"We want our products in that store.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":387991,"text":"And then there's mobile phones."},{"time":390163,"text":"This is an ad for MTN,"},{"time":392003,"text":"which is a South African multinational"},{"time":394645,"text":"active in about 25 countries,"},{"time":397394,"text":"and when they came into Nigeria —"},{"time":398955,"text":"Nigeria is the big dog in Africa."},{"time":400912,"text":"One in seven Africans is a Nigerian,"},{"time":403236,"text":"and so everyone wants in to the mobile phone market"},{"time":405938,"text":"in Nigeria. And when MTN came in, they wanted"},{"time":407972,"text":"to sell the mobile service like I get in the United States"},{"time":410932,"text":"or like people get here in the U.K. or in Europe --"},{"time":414706,"text":"expensive monthly plans, you get a phone,"},{"time":418595,"text":"you pay overages,"},{"time":420595,"text":"you're killed with fees --"},{"time":422723,"text":"and their plan crashed and burned."},{"time":424527,"text":"And they went back to the drawing board, and they retooled,"},{"time":426567,"text":"and they came up with another plan:"},{"time":428071,"text":"We don't sell you the phone,"},{"time":430257,"text":"we don't sell you the monthly plan."},{"time":432087,"text":"We only sell you airtime."},{"time":435223,"text":"And where's the airtime sold?"},{"time":437136,"text":"It's sold at umbrella stands all over the streets,"},{"time":441229,"text":"where people are unregistered, unlicensed,"},{"time":444953,"text":"but MTN makes most of its profits,"},{"time":447658,"text":"perhaps 90 percent of its profits,"},{"time":450345,"text":"from selling through System D, the informal economy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455007,"text":"And where do the phones come from?"},{"time":456843,"text":"Well, they come from here. This is in Guangzhou, China,"},{"time":459717,"text":"and if you go upstairs in this rather sleepy looking"},{"time":463153,"text":"electronics mall, you find the Guangzhou Dashatou"},{"time":467779,"text":"second-hand trade center,"},{"time":470652,"text":"and if you go in there, you follow the guys with the muscles"},{"time":473836,"text":"who are carrying the boxes, and where are they going?"},{"time":476498,"text":"They're going to Eddy in Lagos."},{"time":479315,"text":"Now, most of the phones there are not second-hand at all."},{"time":482019,"text":"The name is a misnomer."},{"time":483326,"text":"Most of them are pirated. They have the name brand"},{"time":486234,"text":"on them, but they're not manufactured by the name brand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489315,"text":"Now, are there downsides to that?"},{"time":491971,"text":"Well, I guess. You know, China has no —"},{"time":495219,"text":"(Laughter) — no intellectual property, right?"},{"time":498511,"text":"Versace without the vowels."},{"time":500412,"text":"Zhuomani instead of Armani."},{"time":502474,"text":"S. Guuuci, and -- (Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":507481,"text":"All around the world this is how products"},{"time":510610,"text":"are being distributed, so, for instance,"},{"time":513130,"text":"in one street market on Rua 25 de Março"},{"time":516289,"text":"in São Paulo, Brazil,"},{"time":518258,"text":"you can buy fake designer glasses."},{"time":521554,"text":"You can buy cloned cologne."},{"time":523617,"text":"You can buy pirated DVDs, of course."},{"time":526392,"text":"You can buy New York Yankees caps"},{"time":529249,"text":"in all sorts of unauthorized patterns."},{"time":532455,"text":"You can buy cuecas baratas, designer underwear"},{"time":535544,"text":"that isn't really manufactured by a designer,"},{"time":537841,"text":"and even pirated evangelical mixtapes. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":542215,"text":"Now, businesses tend to complain about this,"},{"time":544969,"text":"and their, they, I don't want to take away from their"},{"time":548508,"text":"entire validity of complaining about it,"},{"time":550546,"text":"but I did ask a major sneaker manufacturer earlier this year"},{"time":555044,"text":"what they thought about piracy,"},{"time":557941,"text":"and they told me, \"Well, you can't quote me on this,"},{"time":559288,"text":"because if you quote me on this, I have to kill you,\""},{"time":561388,"text":"but they use piracy as market research."},{"time":567092,"text":"The sneaker manufacturer told me that if"},{"time":570316,"text":"they find that Pumas are being pirated, or Adidas"},{"time":574003,"text":"are being pirated and their sneakers aren't being pirated,"},{"time":577289,"text":"they know they've done something wrong. (Laughter)"},{"time":580174,"text":"So it's very important to them to track piracy"},{"time":583251,"text":"exactly because of this, and the people who are buying,"},{"time":585615,"text":"the pirates, are not their customers anyway,"},{"time":587735,"text":"because their customers want the real deal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590467,"text":"Now, there's another problem."},{"time":591960,"text":"This is a real street sign in Lagos, Nigeria."},{"time":595292,"text":"All of System D really doesn't pay taxes, right?"},{"time":598356,"text":"And when I think about that, first of all I think that"},{"time":600161,"text":"government is a social contract between the people and"},{"time":603875,"text":"the government, and if the government isn't transparent,"},{"time":606391,"text":"then the people aren't going to be transparent either,"},{"time":608612,"text":"but also that we're blaming the little guy"},{"time":611660,"text":"who doesn't pay his taxes, and we're not recognizing"},{"time":613597,"text":"that everyone's fudging things all over the world,"},{"time":616370,"text":"including some extremely respected businesses,"},{"time":620403,"text":"and I'll give you one example."},{"time":621543,"text":"There was one company that paid 4,000 bribes"},{"time":625694,"text":"in the first decade of this millennium, and"},{"time":628092,"text":"a million dollars in bribes every business day, right?"},{"time":632993,"text":"All over the world. And that company"},{"time":635288,"text":"was the big German electronics giant Siemens."},{"time":638194,"text":"So this goes on in the formal economy"},{"time":642072,"text":"as well as the informal economy,"},{"time":644270,"text":"so it's wrong of us to blame — and I'm not singling out"},{"time":646400,"text":"Siemens, I'm saying everyone does it. Okay?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":650119,"text":"I just want to end by saying that if Adam Smith"},{"time":653568,"text":"had framed out a theory of the flea market"},{"time":656408,"text":"instead of the free market, what would be some"},{"time":659719,"text":"of the principles?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":661728,"text":"First, it would be to understand that it could be"},{"time":665488,"text":"considered a cooperative, and this is a thought"},{"time":667679,"text":"from the Brazilian legal scholar Roberto Mangabeira Unger."},{"time":672264,"text":"Cooperative development is a way forward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":674857,"text":"Secondly, from the [Austrian] anarchist philosopher Paul Feyerabend,"},{"time":679535,"text":"facts are relative, and what is a massive right"},{"time":683823,"text":"of self-reliance to a Nigerian businessperson"},{"time":686808,"text":"is considered unauthorized and horrible to other people,"},{"time":690819,"text":"and we have to recognize that there are differences"},{"time":692836,"text":"in how people define things and what their facts are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":694893,"text":"And third is, and I'm taking this from"},{"time":697993,"text":"the great American beat poet Allen Ginsberg,"},{"time":701273,"text":"that alternate economies barter and"},{"time":704425,"text":"different kinds of currency, alternate currencies"},{"time":707176,"text":"are also very important, and he talked about"},{"time":710018,"text":"buying what he needed just with his good looks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":713009,"text":"And so I just want to leave you there, and say that"},{"time":716640,"text":"this economy is a tremendous force for global development"},{"time":720856,"text":"and we need to think about it that way."},{"time":722823,"text":"Thank you very much. (Applause)"},{"time":725839,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}